<subSubSection id="C336652FFFB2FFB5FF7DFE48EF94FB81" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9336A4FFB2FFB5FF7DFE48EF8CFCC5" blockId="6.[151,1437,439,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FF7DFE48EF3FFDE5" bold="true" box="[199,308,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Remarks</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FEEAFE48EC24FDE5" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[336,559,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FEEAFE48EC24FDE5" box="[336,559,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Sperchon amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FCABFE48EA73FDE5" author="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H." box="[785,1144,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref7449" refString="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H. (1979) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 10. Mitteilung. Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 6 (105), 243 - 252." type="journal article" year="1979">Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian (1979)</bibRefCitation>
from a karstic spring in 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F846FFB2FFB5FF2DFD93EF63FDC1" box="[151,360,547,574]" country="Iran" name="Lorestan" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Lorestan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33B7634FFB2FFB5FECFFD93EFADFDC2" box="[373,422,548,574]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Later on, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FDA5FD94ECFDFDC1" author="Asadi, M. &amp; Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I." box="[543,758,547,574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="43 - 55" refId="ref7401" refString="Asadi, M., Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I. (2010) A revised survey of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Iran: new synonyms and descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 2628, 43 - 55." type="journal article" year="2010">
Asadi 
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FDD3FD93EC97FDC1" box="[617,668,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the 
<typeStatus id="54978806FFB2FFB5FC04FD94EA2BFDC1" box="[958,1056,547,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FBF3FD94EADBFDC1" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[1097,1232,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FBF3FD94EADBFDC1" box="[1097,1232,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found that in view of the similar shape of the palp and dorsum, III/IV-L-3–5 with numerous pinnate dorsal setae and sclerotized excretory pore the later species matches the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FC8EFDDCEA50FD7A" authority="Koenike, 1895" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[820,1115,619,646]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FC8EFDDCEDA7FD79" box="[820,940,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. hispidus</emphasis>
Koenike, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, a species widely distributed in the Western Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FE70FD38ECDDFD55" author="Di Sabatino, A. &amp; Gerecke, R. &amp; Gledhill, T. &amp; Smit, H." box="[458,726,655,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="2 - 2" refId="ref7835" refString="Di Sabatino, A., Gerecke, R., Gledhill, T. &amp; Smit, H. (2010) Acari: Hydrachnidia II. In: Gerecke, R. (Ed.), Chelicerata: Acari II. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa, Vol. 7, 2 - 2, Elsevier Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, pp. 1 - 234." type="journal article" year="2010">
Di Sabatino 
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FDE3FD27EC80FD55" box="[601,651,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). As a result, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FCD7FD38EA4AFD55" author="Asadi, M. &amp; Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I." box="[877,1089,655,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="43 - 55" refId="ref7401" refString="Asadi, M., Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I. (2010) A revised survey of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Iran: new synonyms and descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 2628, 43 - 55." type="journal article" year="2010">
Asadi 
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FC0CFD27EDECFD55" box="[950,999,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed to place 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FAACFD38EB97FD55" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[1302,1436,655,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FAACFD38EB97FD55" box="[1302,1436,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FED5FD04EFE1FD31" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[367,490,691,717]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FED5FD04EFE1FD31" box="[367,490,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. During our 2017 survey in Northern 
<collectingCountry id="F33B7634FFB2FFB5FC1EFD03EDDAFD32" box="[932,977,692,718]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Iran</collectingCountry>
we collected and successfully barcoded 
<specimenCount id="9D2AFD2DFFB2FFB5FF2DFD60EF40FD0D" box="[151,331,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FECAFD60EFC6FD0D" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[368,461,727,753]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FECAFD60EFC6FD0D" box="[368,461,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like mites that match the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FC4AFD60EA7DFD0D" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[1008,1142,727,753]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FC4AFD60EA7DFD0D" box="[1008,1142,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to the original description, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FE9CFD4CEFBAFCE9" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[294,433,763,789]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FE9CFD4CEFBAFCE9" box="[294,433,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separate from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FD07FD4CED30FCE9" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[701,827,763,789]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FD07FD4CED30FCE9" box="[701,827,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a parallelogram-shaped Cx-IV (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FA8CFD4CEF71FCC5" author="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H." pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref7449" refString="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H. (1979) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 10. Mitteilung. Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 6 (105), 243 - 252." type="journal article" year="1979">Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336A4FFB2FFB5FF7DFCF4EC0CFBA5" blockId="6.[151,1437,439,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">
The final alignment for species delimitation using COI sequence data comprised sequences of 34 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FA8EFCF4EB96FCA1" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1877" box="[1332,1437,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FA8EFCF4EB96FCA1" box="[1332,1437,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Sperchon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens listed in 
<tableCitation id="C6AE031FFFB2FFB5FEC0FCD0EFC4FC7D" box="[378,463,871,897]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,239,872,896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 4. List of Sperchon specimens used in this study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF53662CFFBCFFBBFF2DFCDFECF5FC7C" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" tableUuid="DF53662CFFBCFFBBFF2DFCDFECF5FC7C">Table 4</tableCitation>
and one outgroup, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FD0BFCD0EA67FC7E" authority="(Protz, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Protz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[689,1132,871,898]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FD0BFCD0EDC6FC7D" box="[689,973,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Sperchonopsis verrucosa</emphasis>
(Protz, 1896)
</taxonomicName>
[BOLD 46. M19_16B_1_ G10] from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B7634FFB2FFB5FEA9FC3BEF97FC5A" box="[275,412,908,934]" name="Serbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
to root the tree. The neighbor-joining (NJ) tree is presented in 
<figureCitation id="13172A21FFB2FFB5FBEBFC3CEA9FFC59" box="[1105,1172,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1622,1646]" captionTargetBox="[171,1422,212,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,198,1598]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neighbor-joining tree based on studied Sperchon COI sequences. The optimal tree with the sum of branch length = 1.14769493 is shown. The analysis involved 35 nucleotide sequences. There were a total of 670 positions in the final dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794942" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794942/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
. The COI tree sequence recovered 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FEB5FC18EF9DFC35" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[271,406,943,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FEB5FC18EF9DFC35" box="[271,406,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a sister branch to the clade grouping COI sequences found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FB3DFC18EB09FC35" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[1159,1282,943,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FB3DFC18EB09FC35" box="[1159,1282,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A21FFB2FFB5FAAEFC18EB50FC35" box="[1300,1371,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1622,1646]" captionTargetBox="[171,1422,212,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,198,1598]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neighbor-joining tree based on studied Sperchon COI sequences. The optimal tree with the sum of branch length = 1.14769493 is shown. The analysis involved 35 nucleotide sequences. There were a total of 670 positions in the final dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794942" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794942/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). The average genetic distance between the COI sequence of the 
<specimenCount id="9D2AFD2DFFB2FFB5FCF7FC64EA0FFC11" box="[845,1028,979,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FB8BFC64EAB0FC11" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[1073,1211,979,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FB8BFC64EAB0FC11" box="[1073,1211,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B7634FFB2FFB5FABDFC63EB3FFC12" box="[1287,1332,980,1006]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D2AFD2DFFB2FFB5FAC8FC63EF07FBED" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FE8EFC40EFA5FBED" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[308,430,1015,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FE8EFC40EFA5FBED" box="[308,430,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B7634FFB2FFB5FE4CFC4FEC74FBEE" box="[502,639,1016,1042]" name="Serbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
was estimated to 16.5% K2P indicating a long independent history of these two species. Therefore, we propose to resurrect 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FD4DFBACEB22FBC9" authority="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian, 1979" authorityName="Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian" authorityYear="1979" box="[759,1321,1051,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FD4DFBACEDD9FBC9" box="[759,978,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Sperchon amuzgari</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B55FFB2FFB5FC60FBACEB22FBC9" author="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H." box="[986,1321,1051,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" pagination="243 - 252" refId="ref7449" refString="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H. (1979) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 10. Mitteilung. Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 6 (105), 243 - 252." type="journal article" year="1979">Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species distinct from 
<emphasis id="B958EAB6FFB2FFB5FE3CFB88EC0CFBA5" box="[390,519,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D27FFB2FFB5FE3CFB88EC08FBA5" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1895" box="[390,515,1087,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">S. hispidus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
